  "sourceCode": "Employer Portal",
  "title": "Student Care Teacher",
  "description": "<p><strong>Job Responsibilities</strong></p><ul><li>Responsible for the preparation and upkeep of teaching resources, arrangement, appearance and learning environment of the classroom.</li><li>Supervise and guide the primary children with their homework</li><li>Plan and deliver activities, lesson and programmes, such as character development programmes in a creative and interesting manner to encourage students’ participation</li><li>Organise enrichment workshops that can help promote the overall development of the children</li><li>Curate creative activities to develop skills and expand mindsets in the areas of innovation, critical thinking and problem-solving skills.</li><li>Engage children in outdoor play that serves to build psychomotor skills</li><li>Daily administration - attendance, collection of forms, health and safety, etc.</li><li>Ensure the safety and wellbeing of the students.</li><li>Liaise with parents and guardians regarding children’s learning progress and behaviour in class</li></ul><p><strong>Other Requirements</strong></p><ul><li><strong>Possess a Polytechnic Diploma in relevant discipline or WSQ Student Care certification</strong></li><li><strong>At least 2 years of experience in teaching children, preferably at primary level</strong></li><li>Prior work experience with children with special needs is an added advantage</li><li>A team player with good communication and classroom management skills</li><li>Patient and passionate about teaching children with special needs</li><li>Good understanding in primary school curriculum</li></ul>",
